thread.title: 7-Eleven customer hurt during robbery

author: democratandchronicle.com
title: 7-Eleven customer hurt during robbery
text:
A customer was injured during an attempted robbery at a 7-Eleven Store in Rochester on Saturday. Police responded to the 7-Eleven Store at 890 Monroe Ave. at 5:42 p.m. for a report of someone armed with a knife robbing the store, Rochester Police Lt. Jason Elwood said.
According to Elwood, several customers intervened and detained the suspect until police arrived. During the attempted robbery, one of the customers sustained minor abrasions.
He was transported to the hospital for treatment and is expected to be treated and released, Elwood said.
WCLEVELAND@Gannett.com
